-- South Korea Says Uncertainty Persists on Europe Crisis, Oil Cost
-- B y   E u n k y u n g   S e o
-- 2012-04-05T01:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-05/south-korea-says-uncertainty-persists-on-europe-crisis-oil-cost.html
Uncertainty over  South Korea ’s
economic outlook persists due to high  oil prices  and the ongoing
European debt crisis, the  finance ministry  said.  The nation’s economy shows some signs of improvement while
inflation has moderated to “some” extent, the ministry said in
its monthly economic assessment released today.  -- Editor: Seyoon Kim,  Jim McDonald .  To contact the reporter on this story:
